ited Air Group Flight 3949]] crashed into a mountain following a loss of control after fuel was selected from the left wing tanks to counter a left wing-low attitude.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= RA-85164|id= 19951207-0|access-date= 23 December 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1996|8|29}}\n|align=center|RA-85621\n|align=center|Tu-154M\n| {{Flagicon|NOR}} [[Operafjellet]]\n|align=center|{{nts|141}}/141\n| [[Vnukovo Airlines Flight 2801]] crashed into a mountain on final approach due to navigation errors. This accident remains the worst in Norway.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= RA-85621|id= 19960829-0|access-date= 23 December 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1997|9|13}}\n|align=center|''11+02''\n|align=center|Tu-154M\n|rowspan=\"2\" |{{Flagicon|NAM}} off [[Namibia]]\n|rowspan=\"2\" align=center|{{nts|33}}/33\n|rowspan=\"2\" |[[1997 Namibia mid-air collision|German Air Force Flight 074]] collided in mid-air with a USAF C-141 due to pilot and ATC errors.\n|rowspan=\"2\" align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= 11+02|id= 19970913-0|access-date= 4 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{ASN accident|title= 65-9405|id= 19970913-1|access-date= 4 December 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|''65-9405''\n|align=center|[[Lockheed C-141 Starlifter|C-141]]\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1997|12|15}}\n|align=center|EY-85281\n|align=center|Tu-154B-1\n| {{flagicon|UAE}} [[Sharjah (city)|Sharjah]]\n|align=center|{{nts|85}}/86\n| [[Tajikistan Airlines Flight 3183]] crashed in the desert due to pilot error and crew fatigue.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= EY-85281|id= 19971215-0|access-date= 23 December 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|1998|8|29}}\n|align=center|CU-T1264\n|align=center|Tu-154M\n| {{Flagicon|Ecuador}} [[Quito]]\n|align=center|{{nts|10+70}}/91\n| [[Cubana de Aviaci\u00f3n Flight 389]] failed to take off and overran the runway, crashing into a soccer field. Following problems before takeo