01 | last1 = Wines | first1 = Michael|access-date=20 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170312020347/http://www.nytimes.com/2001/10/14/world/after-9-days-ukraine-says-its-missile-hit-a-russian-jet.html|archive-date=12 March 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|2002|2|12}}\n|align=center|EP-MBS\n|align=center|Tu-154M\n| {{Flagicon|IRN}} near [[Sarab-e Do Rah]]\n|align=center|{{nts|119}}/119\n| [[Iran Air Tours Flight 956]] struck a mountain on approach.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= EP-MBS|id= 20020212-0|access-date= 28 December 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|2002|2|20}}\n|align=center|EP-LBX\n|align=center|Tu-154M\n| {{Flagicon|IRN}} [[Mashhad International Airport]]\n|align=center|{{nts|0}}\n|Landed hard, suffering substantial damage. The aircraft was ferried to Vnukovo for repairs where the nose gear collapsed while the aircraft was being towed. The aircraft was written off and used for spare parts.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= EP-LBX|id= 20020220-1|access-date= 28 December 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|2002|07|1}}\n|align=center|RA-85816\n|align=center|Tu-154M\n|rowspan=\"2\"|{{flagicon|DEU}} over [[\u00dcberlingen]]\n|rowspan=\"2\" align=center|{{nts|2+69}}/69\n|rowspan=\"2\" |[[\u00dcberlingen mid-air collision|Bashkirian Airlines Flight 2937]] collided in mid-air with DHL Flight 611 due to errors of communication between instruction from ATC and [[Traffic collision avoidance system]].\n|rowspan=\"2\" align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= RA-85816|id= 20020701-0|access-date= 28 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{ASN accident|title= A9C-DHL|id= 20020701-1|access-date= 28 December 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|A9C-DHL\n|align=center|757-200\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|2004|8|24}}\n|align=center|RA-85556\n|align=center|Tu-154B-2\n| {{Flagicon|RUS}} near [[Gluboki]]\n|align=center|{{nts|46}}/46\n| [[2004 Russian aircraft bombings|Sibir Airlines Flight 1047]] crashed after it was bombed in mid-air by a suicide bomber, along with a Tu-134 on the same day.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|type=Criminal|title= RA-85556|id= 20040824-1|access-date= 28 December 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|2006|8|22}}\n|align=center|RA-85185\n|align=center|Tu-154M\n| {{Flagicon|UKR}} near [[Donetsk]]\n|align=center|{{nts|170}}/170\n| [[Pulkovo Airlines Flight 612]] stalled and crashed after the crew attempted to fly over a storm front. The aircraft entered turbulence and later stalled. The aircraft entered a [[Spin (aerodynamics)#Phases|flat spin]] and then struck the ground.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= RA-85185|id= 20060822-0|access-date= 28 December 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|2006|09|1}}\n|align=center|EP-MCF\n|align=center|Tu-154M\n| {{Flagicon|IRN}} Mashhad International Airport\n|align=center|{{nts|28}}/148\n| [[Iran Air Tours Flight 945]] suffered a mishap while landing, possibly due to a blown nosegear tire. The aircraft swerved off the runway.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= EP-MCF|id= 20060901-0|access-date= 28 December 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|2008|6|30}}\n|align=center|RA-85667\n|align=center|Tu-154M\n| {{Flagicon|RUS}} [[Pulkovo Airport]]\n|align=center|{{nts|0}}/112\n|The number one engine suffered an uncontained failure during takeoff and takeoff was aborted. The aircraft was parked at Pulkovo Airport after the incident and was broken up in August 2009.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= RA-85667|id= 20080630-1|access-date= 28 December 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{{dts|format=dmy|2009|7|15}}\n|align=center|EP-CPG\n|align=center|Tu-154M\n| {{Flagicon|IRN}} near [[Qazvin]]\n|align=center|{{nts|168}}/168\n| [[Caspian Airlines Flight 7908]] lost control and crashed following an engine fire.\n|align=center|<ref>{{ASN accident|title= EP-CPG|id= 20090715-0|access-date= 28 December 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=center|{