79 [[action film]] revolving around the exploits of a Soviet Tu-154 crew on an international flight, the first Soviet film in the [[disaster film|disaster]] genre.\n\n==See also==\n{{aircontent\n|related=\n* [[Tupolev Tu-155]]\n* [[Tupolev Tu-204]]\n|similar aircraft=\n* [[Boeing 727]]\n* [[Hawker Siddeley Trident]]\n* [[Yakovlev Yak-42]]\n|lists=\n* [[List of civil aircraft]]\n* [[List of jet airliners]]\n|see also=\n}}\n\n==References==\n\n===Citations===\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n===Bibliography===\n* Dmitriy Komissarov, ''Tupolev Tu-154, The USSR's Medium-Range Jet Airliner'', (Hinckley, UK, 2007) {{ISBN|1857802411}}\n* Yefin Gordon and Vladimir Rigmant, ''OKB Tupolev, A History of the Design Bureau and its Aircraft'', translated by Alexander Boyd, edited by Dmitriy Komissarov (Hinckley, UK, 2005) {{ISBN|1-85780-214-4}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons|Tupolev Tu-154}}\n* [http://www.airliners.net/photo/Slovakia-Government/Tupolev-Tu-154M/1087183 Image of Tu-154M flight-deck]\n* [http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/europe/2081143.stm BBC: Tu-154: The backbone of Russian fleets]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20100413175703/http://www.plastikowe.pl/galerie/tu-154m Gallery of Polish VIP variant of Tu-154M used by 36. Special Transport Aviation Regiment in ''Plastikowe.pl'' magazine]\n\n{{Portalbar|Russia|Soviet Union|Aviation}}\n{{Tupolev aircraft}}\n\n[[Category:Tupolev aircraft|Tu-154]]\n[[Category:1960s Soviet airliners]]\n[[Category:Trijets]]\n[[Category:Low-wing aircraft]]\n[[Category:T-tail aircraft]]\n[[Category:Aircraft first flown in 1968]]\n", "name_user": "Panama2005", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eAircraft on display:triple [[[", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tupolev_Tu-154"}
